---
title: Pydantic v2 — Model Definition & Validation Sequence
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant BM   as BaseModel<br/>(main.py)
    participant Meta as ModelMetaclass<br/>(_model_construction.py)
    participant GS   as GenerateSchema<br/>(_generate_schema.py)
    participant Core as pydantic-core<br/>(Rust SchemaValidator)

    Note over User,Core: Phase 1 — Class Definition (happens once at import time)

    User  ->>  BM   : class MyModel(BaseModel):<br/>  name: str<br/>  age: int
    BM    ->>  Meta : __init_subclass__()
    Meta  ->>  GS   : generate_schema(fields, config)
    GS    ->>  GS   : resolve type annotations<br/>handle generics, validators,<br/>discriminated unions
    GS    -->> Meta : CoreSchema (Python dict IR)
    Meta  ->>  Core : SchemaValidator(core_schema)
    Core  -->> Meta : compiled SchemaValidator
    Meta  -->> BM   : __pydantic_validator__ attached

    Note over User,Core: Phase 2 — Instance Validation (happens on every call)

    User  ->>  BM   : MyModel(name="Alice", age=30)
    BM    ->>  Core : validate_python({"name": "Alice", "age": 30})
    Core  ->>  Core : run Rust validator tree<br/>(coerce, check constraints,<br/>run field validators)
    alt valid data
        Core  -->> BM   : validated dict
        BM    -->> User : MyModel instance
    else invalid data
        Core  -->> BM   : ValidationError (with loc + msg)
        BM    -->> User : raises ValidationError
    end

    Note over User,Core: Phase 3 — Serialization

    User  ->>  BM   : model.model_dump()
    BM    ->>  Core : SchemaSerializer.to_python(model)
    Core  -->> BM   : plain dict
    BM    -->> User : {"name": "Alice", "age": 30}
